.TH ACMERS 1 "2026-06-12" "acmers 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
acmers \- zero-dependency ACME client for SSL/TLS certificate automation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B acmers
\fIcommand\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBacmers\fR is a minimal-dependency Rust CLI for automatic SSL/TLS
certificate issuance and renewal via the ACME protocol (RFC 8555).
It supports DNS-01 challenge validation for 200+ DNS providers,
ported from the acme.sh project.
.PP
Single binary, zero runtime dependencies beyond glibc.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBregister\fR \-\-email \fIaddr\fR [\-\-test]
Register a new ACME account. Use \fB--test\fR for staging environment.
.TP
\fBissue\fR \fIdomain\fR... \-\-dns \fIprovider\fR \-\-email \fIaddr\fR [\-\-test] [\-\-dnssleep \fIsecs\fR]
Issue a certificate for one or more domains using DNS-01 challenge.
The \fB--dns\fR flag selects the DNS provider (see \fBlist-providers\fR).
Use \fB--test\fR for staging, \fB--dnssleep\fR to wait for DNS propagation.
.TP
\fBrenew\fR \fIdomain\fR [\-\-test]
Renew an existing certificate for the given domain.
.TP
\fBrevoke\fR \fIdomain\fR
Revoke a certificate for the given domain.
.TP
\fBlist\-providers\fR
List all available DNS providers with their required environment variables.
.TP
\fBcron\fR
Run certificate renewal check (designed for cron/systemd timer use).
.SH DNS PROVIDERS
acmers supports 200+ DNS providers. Each provider requires specific
environment variables for authentication. Run \fBacmers list-providers\fR
to see the full list and required variables.
.PP
Common providers and their environment variables:
.TP
\fBcloudflare\fR
\fBCF_Token\fR or \fBCF_Key\fR + \fBCF_Email\fR
.TP
\fBdigitalocean\fR
\fBDO_API_KEY\fR
.TP
\fBroute53\fR
\fBAWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID\fR + \fBAWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY\fR
.TP
\fBduckdns\fR
\fBDuckDNS_Token\fR
.TP
\fBhe\fR (Hurricane Electric)
\fBHE_Username\fR + \fBHE_Password\fR
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.acmers/
Configuration and account data directory.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
All DNS provider credentials are passed via environment variables.
No credentials are stored on disk beyond the ACME account key.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Error occurred (configuration, provider, or ACME protocol error).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR certbot (1),
.BR openssl (1)
.PP
Project homepage: \fIhttps://github.com/josacar/acmers\fR
